    "body": "## Steps to reproduce\r\n1. Build and install the latest debug build from 10/11 (build 11 GV 95.0a1-20211005094529).\r\n2. Add a shortcut to the app's homescreen.\r\n3. Go to the homescreen, and tap on the created shortcut, and observe.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nTapping on the shortcut, opens the page in a new tab, without glitches.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nTapping on the shortcut displays briefly the \"tapping\" action, by highlighting the thumbnail and the title of the shortcut - please see the slow-motion short video.\r\n\r\n### Device information\r\n* Android device: Google Pixel (Android 10)\r\n* Focus version: the latest debug build from 10/11 (build 11 GV 95.0a1-20211005094529)\r\n* Reproducible on both light, and dark theme, but it is more obvious in light theme.\r\n* It was not reproducible on the debug build from 10/8\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40694158/136755157-bd2e57ba-184b-4457-ab06-d2aa9dffcceb.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n",
